item.title: Is five years the dating sweet spot to create a long-term relationship?
item.description:
Is five years the dating sweet spot to create a long-term relationship?

While there are no set rules when it comes to relationships, there are a few stages that will likely repeat each time you fall in love. After the first date, there will probably be a short period of time when all you can wonder about is if they like you as much as you like them.

item.title: How do I extend your life into old age
item.description:
How do I extend your life into old age

Do you want to live to be 100? Maybe you can. At the very least, you can extend your life by 12 years past the American average if you change how you do things just a little bit. That's the surprising lesson that National Geographic writer Dan Buettner shares in his engaging TED Talk "How to Live to Be 100+".
